AUDIO: 'The avatar variant of Runway\'s GWM1 general world model, streaming over WebRTC. The session is a live WebRTC call between the LiveKit room and Runway. Okay, but I want to try something. I\'m'

[01:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'going to talk for a few seconds, and I want everyone to watch you and not me. Most AI avatars, they freeze the second the agent stops talking. That glassy stare, they\'re just waiting for their'

[01:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'next turn to speak. Watch this one while I keep talking. The eyes, the little nods, the small head movements, all of this is happening live. So, what were you doing just then? Exactly that. I get expression, eye'

[01:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'movement, and gestures while I\'m listening, not just while I\'m speaking. That\'s the difference between a face that\'s alive and a face that\'s buffering. Yep, that is the hard part. Want to walk through how I actually plug'

[01:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'into a LiveKit agent? For sure. LiveKit has a general avatar pattern. An avatar worker joins the LiveKit room as a secondary participant. The agent\'s TTS audio gets routed to the worker instead'

[01:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'of straight to the room, and the worker publishes synchronized audio and lip-sync video back. From the front end, the agent shows up as two participants with one identity. The LiveKit agent'

[02:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'still owns the conversational stack. Runway provides the visual layer, audio in, avatar video out, but the STT, LLM, and TTS, they stay exactly where they are.'

[02:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'And the agent code itself, how much actually changes? Just three lines. You add the Runway extra to the LiveKit agent\'s install. You build a Runway avatar session with a preset ID like cat character or a custom'

[02:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'avatar ID, and you await the avatar start before awaiting the session start, and that order matters because the plugin rewires the agent\'s audio output to point at the avatar worker.'

[02:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'What about the front end? That\'s usually the next question. There\'s nothing new to write. A standard LiveKit React front end with voice use voice assistant already resolves the'

[02:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'avatar\'s audio and video tracks. The worker shows up with the kind equals agent, and the LK publish on behalf points at the agent identity. So, the existing components handle the layout'

[03:12] [scene:talk]
